theorem
Th20: (( ( 0. X ) rExpSeq ) is  norm_summable & ( Sum ( ( 0. X ) rExpSeq ) ) = ( 1. X ))
proof
defpred X[ set ]
 means
( ( Partial_Sums ||. ( ( 0. X ) rExpSeq ) .|| ) . $1 ) = 1;
A1: (for n being Nat holds (X[ n ] implies X[ ( n + 1 ) ]))
proof
let n being Nat;
assume that
A2: ( ( Partial_Sums ||. ( ( 0. X ) rExpSeq ) .|| ) . n ) = 1;
A3: n in ( NAT ) by ORDINAL1:def 12;
hence ( ( Partial_Sums ||. ( ( 0. X ) rExpSeq ) .|| ) . ( n + 1 ) ) = ( 1 + ( ||. ( ( 0. X ) rExpSeq ) .|| . ( n + 1 ) ) ) by A2,SERIES_1:def 1
.= ( 1 + ||. ( ( ( 0. X ) rExpSeq ) . ( n + 1 ) ) .|| ) by NORMSP_0:def 4
.= ( 1 + ||. ( ( ( 1 / ( n + 1 ) ) * ( 0. X ) ) * ( ( ( 0. X ) rExpSeq ) . n ) ) .|| ) by A3,CKB26:1
.= ( 1 + ||. ( ( 0. X ) * ( ( ( 0. X ) rExpSeq ) . n ) ) .|| ) by LOPBAN_3:38
.= ( 1 + ||. ( 0. X ) .|| ) by LOPBAN_3:38
.= ( 1 + ( 0 ) ) by LOPBAN_3:38
.= 1;
end;
( ( Partial_Sums ||. ( ( 0. X ) rExpSeq ) .|| ) . ( 0 ) ) = ( ||. ( ( 0. X ) rExpSeq ) .|| . ( 0 ) ) by SERIES_1:def 1
.= ||. ( ( ( 0. X ) rExpSeq ) . ( 0 ) ) .|| by NORMSP_0:def 4
.= ||. ( 1. X ) .|| by CKB26:1
.= 1 by LOPBAN_3:38;
then A4: X[ ( 0 ) ];
A5: (for n being Nat holds X[ n ]) from NAT_1:sch 2(A4,A1);
( Partial_Sums ||. ( ( 0. X ) rExpSeq ) .|| ) is  constant
proof
take 1;
let n being Nat;
thus thesis by A5;
end;
then A6: ||. ( ( 0. X ) rExpSeq ) .|| is  summable by SERIES_1:def 2;
defpred X[ set ]
 means
( ( Partial_Sums ( ( 0. X ) rExpSeq ) ) . $1 ) = ( 1. X );
A7: (for n holds (X[ n ] implies X[ ( n + 1 ) ]))
proof
let n;
assume ( ( Partial_Sums ( ( 0. X ) rExpSeq ) ) . n ) = ( 1. X );
hence ( ( Partial_Sums ( ( 0. X ) rExpSeq ) ) . ( n + 1 ) ) = ( ( 1. X ) + ( ( ( 0. X ) rExpSeq ) . ( n + 1 ) ) ) by BHSP_4:def 1
.= ( ( 1. X ) + ( ( ( 1 / ( n + 1 ) ) * ( 0. X ) ) * ( ( ( 0. X ) rExpSeq ) . n ) ) ) by CKB26:1
.= ( ( 1. X ) + ( ( 0. X ) * ( ( ( 0. X ) rExpSeq ) . n ) ) ) by LOPBAN_3:38
.= ( ( 1. X ) + ( 0. X ) ) by LOPBAN_3:38
.= ( 1. X ) by LOPBAN_3:38;
end;
( ( Partial_Sums ( ( 0. X ) rExpSeq ) ) . ( 0 ) ) = ( ( ( 0. X ) rExpSeq ) . ( 0 ) ) by BHSP_4:def 1
.= ( 1. X ) by CKB26:1;
then A8: X[ ( 0 ) ];
(for n holds X[ n ]) from NAT_1:sch 1(A8,A7);
hence thesis by A6,CKB5:1,LOPBAN_3:def 3;
end;
